{{COI|date=January 2014}} {{Infobox university | name = Cyryx College | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = School of Business.png | image_size = thumb | image_alt = School of Business | caption = | latin_name = | other_name = <!-- or: | other_names = --> | former_name = <!-- or: | former_names = --> | motto = | motto_lang = | mottoeng = | type = Private College | established = {{start date|1993|08|24}} | closed = <!-- {{end date|YYYY}} --> | founder = | parent = | affiliation = Help University of Malaysia | religious_affiliation = | academic_affiliation = | endowment = | budget = | officer_in_charge = | chairman = | chairperson = | chancellor = | president = | vice-president = | superintendent = | provost = | vice_chancellor = | rector = | principal = | dean = | director = | head_label = | head = | academic_staff = 65 | administrative_staff = | students = 1500 | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | other = | address = <!-- Please discuss before using --> | city = Malé City | state = | province = | country = Maldives | postcode = <!-- or: | postalcode = --><!-- or: | zipcode = --> | coordinates = | campus = 3 | language = | free_label = | free = | colors = <!-- or: | colours = --> | athletics = | sports = | athletics_nickname = <!-- or: | athletics_nicknames = --><!-- or: | sports_nickname = --><!-- or: | sports_nicknames = --> | mascot = <!-- or: | mascots = --> | sporting_affiliations = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | logo = | logo_size = | logo_alt = | footnotes = }}
'''Cyryx College''' is a private college in [[Malé]] City, [[Maldives]]. Cyryx College has been in operation since 1993. Cyryx College is the longest serving private college in the Maldives, with the most Maldives Qualification Authority (MQA) certified courses in the education sector.{{citation needed|date=January 2014}}<ref name=cyryxcollege>{{cite web|title=Cyryx College|url=http://www.cyryxcollege.edu.mv/|publisher=cyryxcollege.edu.mv|accessdate=2 February 2014}}</ref><ref name="/studyworldinfo">{{cite web|title=Search Results Cyryx College, Maldives|url=http://studyworldinfo.com/admission/index.php/cyryx-college-maldives-admission-procedure-eligibility-criteria/|publisher=/studyworldinfo.com|accessdate=2 February 2014}}</ref>
== History == Cyryx College began on 24 August 1993. Starting with 4 computers and 6 students, Cyryx currently caters to over 1,500 students and employs over 65 academic and support staff members. Cyryx College offers certificates, diplomas, and degrees in Information Technology, Management, and Multimedia.
== Facilities ==
Cyryx College operates 3 campuses: the Maafannu campus houses the School of Information Technology, the Machangolhi campus houses the School of Business, and the Galolhu campus houses the School of Multimedia Arts and Design.<ref name=muazzafu>{{cite web|title=Cyryx College – School of Finance & Business Management|url=http://www.muazzafu.com/place/cyryx-college-school-of-finance-business-management/|publisher=muazzafu.com|accessdate=2 February 2014}}</ref>
